term_inventory_greek.meaning:
abomination, something detestable
an abomination, an abominable thing, detestable thing Mt. 24:15; Mk. 13:14;
idolatry with all its pollution, Lk. 16:15; Rev. 17:4, 5; 21:27*

(middle) to abhor, detest;
(passive) to be vile, abhorrent
to abominate, loathe, detest, abhor, Rom. 2:22; passive to be abominable, detestable, abhorrent, vile Rev. 21:8*
